result.execSummary:
The defendant Michael N Ellenberger was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Possess w/ Intent-THC(>200-1000g), a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 961.41(1m)(h)2.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Michael N Ellenberger in court with attorney Jessica Shank Phelps.  Craig Lambert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Plea hearing at 01-11-2016 10:00 am

Defendant Michael N Ellenberger in court with attorney Jessica Shank Phelps.  Craig Lambert appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Nathan Dean sworn in.  Testifies he is a deputy with the Wood County Sheriff's Department.  Testifies to contact with defendant during incident.  Witness identifies the defendant in the courtroom.  Witness testifies to interaction with defendant and describes scene where defendant was located. Witness describes items found in backpack. 
Cross by Attorney Phelps.  Witness testifies that initial stop with defendant was for welfare check.  
Redirect by Attorney Lambert. 
Recross by Attorney Phelps.
Court denies motion.
Notice of Motion and Motion to Suppress
for Preliminary Hearing and Arraignment held September 16, 2015.  (Denise A. Zamow, Court Reporter)
Jury trial - 12 person at 12-15-2015 08:30 am
Attorney Jessica Shank Phelps in court.  Nicholas Grode appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Not guilty plea.    Bond continued

2:18 Attorney Jessica Shank Phelps in court.  Nicholas Grode appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  

Nathan Dean is sworn as a witness.  Testifies to his employment with Wood County Sheriff's Dept.  Testifies to observing of a male subject laying on porch and identifies Ellenberger in the courtroom as the male subject.  Testifies to conversation with Ellenberger.  Testifies to backpack found and to Ellenberger indicating initially that it was not his backpack.  Ellenberger eventually admitted that the backpack was his.  Testifies to seeing a green leafy substance in the backpack.  Testifies to the green leafy substance being tested positively for marijuana.  Testifies to other items found in the backpack including a "Dab".  Believes marijuana was packaged in order to deliver and explains why.  Testifies to where contact was made.  

Atty Phelps cross examines the witness.  Testifies to the span of time between when Ellenberger denied the backpack was his and when he admitted it was his.  Requested to search the backpack but Ellenberger stated he could not.  

Redirect by Atty Grode.  Ellenberger was holding the backpack when he saw the green leafy substance.  Testifies to when he searched the backpack.

Probable cause is found.  Court proceeds to Arraignment.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for October 23, 2015 at 10:00 am.
